<TITLE> 2 accused in SI Gautam killing remanded </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 27 (bdbews24.com)  A Dhaka court on Tuesday granted police four days to question Zakir Hossain and Ali Haider in relation to the killing of sub inspector Gautam killing. Detective Branch inspector Ruhul Amin presented the two men to the court and requested seven days remand. Dhaka's Chief Metropolitan Magistrate Ismail Hossain granted four days remand, the police's general recording officer of the court sub inspector Shakhawat Hossain confirmed to bdnews24.com. The police said they needed to take the men into custody to identify those who financed and ordered the killing. The police officer, based at Bangshal Police Station, was shot dead at Dholaikhal on Apr 20 midnight while coming back home after duty. RAB on Sunday arrested Zakir Hossain alias Kailya Zakir, 25, and Ali Haider from the city's Jatrabari and Lalmohan Saha Street areas. Shakhawat said another accused in the case Ahmed Ali alias Haider Ali alias Hadi, who had been arrested by the police, gave a confessional statement to the court on Saturday. bd
